attributes.gcd: Refers to the date as on which the snapshot of source data extracted for processing.

Refers to the source system from where data is extracted. Data can be sourced from multiple sources, this column will Refers to the source code from where the data is extracted for this extraction date.

Refers to the unique code for Frequency Distribution for the UOM. For example Frequency modeling supports Binomial, Negative Binomial and Poisson distribution. List of values of this column is referred from DIM_DISTRIBUTION_FITTING_TYPE.V_DISTR_FITTING_TYPE_CODE.
Refers to the record creation date. It has been added to all catalog entities to enable partitioning and archival.
Refers to the run identifier for a set of Records participating in the particular Run with the Run Execution identifier. This is a combination of Run Main Identifier and Run Execution Identifier.

Refers to the unique code for Severity Distribution for the UOM. This column shall hold distribution code for single severity models as well as Body distribution for EVT Models. List of values of this column is referred from DIM_DISTRIBUTION_FITTING_TYPE.V_DISTR_FITTING_TYPE_CODE.

Refers to the unique code for tail Severity Distribution for the UOM. This column shall hold distribution code for tail distribution for EVT Models. List of values of this column is referred from DIM_DISTRIBUTION_FITTING_TYPE.V_DISTR_FITTING_TYPE_CODE.

Flag indicates whether the parameter downloaded is for a Tail Severity  Distribution or not. In case of Frequency Modeling Parameters, this column should be -1. In case of Severity Modeling Parameters this column should be either Y or N. List of values are Y,N.

Refers to the threshold probability (0 to 1) for EVT Models.  This is the threshold percentile at which data is segregated into body and tail. This input value should be provided when F_SEV_TAIL_DIST = 'Y'.

Refers to the unique code for Unit of Measure for which parameters are being downloaded. UOMs are defined through AMHM. List of values of this column is referred from Unit Of Measures Dimension table and Unit Of Measure Code column. UOM  is the granularity at which frequency and severity modelling happens. UOM Mapping can be defined at granularity of Line of Business, Event Type, risk category, etc. Combination of members of these source hierarchies are assigned unique Unit of Measure code.
